body:
by **odysseus9672**:

<pre>What steps will reproduce the problem?
Paste this code into a .go file in emacs: 
if line[0] != &quot;|&quot; { //We've read past the header
	_, err = f.seek( curpos, os.SEEK_SET );
	if err != nil {
		return err;
	}
}

(line is a string, and f is a file).  Emacs does not correctly match the braces that
begin and end the if clause.


Which operating system are you using?
Mac OS X 10.6.8, using AquaMacs Emacs 2.3 and command line emacs 23.1.1. 


Which revision are you using?  (hg identify)
32a5db196298 (release-branch.r60) release/release.r60.2</pre>
